This module provides utilities for interacting with the Firebase Admin SDK, enabling server-side access to Firebase services like Firestore.

## Key Exports

*   **`getAdminApp()`**: Initializes and returns the Firebase Admin `App` instance. It prioritizes using an existing initialized app to prevent multiple initializations. It expects Firebase credentials (`FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`, `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL`, `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY`) to be configured in the environment variables.
*   **`getAdminDb()`**: Returns a singleton instance of the Firestore client (`Firestore`). It uses `getAdminApp()` to get the Firebase app instance and initializes the Firestore client only once, caching it for subsequent calls.

## Usage

This module is intended to be used in server-side environments (e.g., API routes, serverless functions) where secure access to Firebase is required.

```typescript
import { getAdminDb } from './firebase-admin';

async function getUserData(userId: string) {
  const db = getAdminDb();
  const userRef = db.collection('users').doc(userId);
  const doc = await userRef.get();
  if (!doc.exists) {
    console.log('No such document!');
    return null;
  } else {
    return doc.data();
  }
}
```
